headline: Trump puts pressure on Netflix board, Domino's stock rises on Q4
summary: Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Brooke DiPalma tracks several of the day's top trending stock tickers, including Variety reporting that Paramount Skydance (PSKY) plans to up its bid for Warner Bros. Discovery (WBD) while President Trump puts pressure on Netflix (NFLX) to fire his former US ambassador and national security advisor, Susan Rice, from the streaming giant's board. Novo Nordisk (NVO) stock is falling on Monday after its weight-loss drug underperformed compared to Eli Lilly's own GLP-1 in a clinical trial. And, Domino's Pizza (DPZ) shares getting a lift higher when the chain topped fourth quarter revenue estimates.
